definitions.definition: A quotation ; a statement attributed to a person.
examples: She loved reading quotes of famous people.

definitions.definition: A summary of work to be done with a set price.
examples: After going over the hefty quotes , the board decided it was cheaper to have the project executed by its own staff.

definitions.definition: A price set and offered (by the potential seller) for a financial security or commodity .
